Lower-mid Sacramento River Flow to Floodplain Habitat Area Relationship

A dataset containing the floodplain habitat area in acres as a function of flow in cubic feet per second

lower_mid_sacramento_river_floodplain

Format

dataframe with 240 rows and 3 variables:

flow_cfs

integer flow value in cubic feet per second

FR_floodplain_acres

fall run floodplain acreage

watershed

name of watershed

Source

missing

Details

The habitat area was derived from a HEC-RAS 1D model. The CVPIA Lower-mid Sacramento River extends from Wilkins Slough to the American River (58.0 mi). This reach overlaps with two of the study's, Battle Creek to the confluence with the Feather River (189.1 mi) and the confluence with the Feather River to Freeport (33.4 mi). To scale the study's results to CVPIA's extents, we calculate the proportion of the Lower-mid Sacramento River above (34%) and below (66%) the Feather River. The floodplain acerage at a given flow is the weighted average of the floodplain area per river mile within each study.
